article.headline: Wagner 63, Rhode Island 61
article.story: SOUTH KINGSTOWN, R.I. (AP) -- Mark Porter matched a career-high with 22 points as Wagner held off Rhode Island for a 63-61 win Saturday. Wagner (6-1) led by nine points with less than two minutes to play, but Rhode Island's Dawan Robinson closed the gap by scoring seven of his 12 points. Jamaal Wise hit a pair of free throws to pull Rhode Island within 61-60 with 17 seconds left. After DeEarnest McLemore made two free throws to extend Wagner's lead to 63-60, Jimmy Baron missed two three-pointers in the final four seconds that would have tied or won the game for Rhode Island. The last one was a desperation heave from beyond mid-court. McLemore scored five of his nine points from the foul line. Wise led Rhode Island (5-3) with 15 points. Porter scored off a Rhode Island turnover to give Wagner a 48-46 lead with 7:51 left, and they led the rest of the way. In the first half, Wagner held Rhode Island without a field goal for a stretch of more than nine minutes, but the game was tied 23-23 at halftime.
